
Create a new map.

USAGE
  create-map <command>

ARGUMENT FLAGS
  --map.display-name                 [O]   string               Human-readable name of the map
  --map.description                  [O]   string               Description for this map
  --map.site                         [R]   string               Site where this map was created
  --map.type                         [RI]  enum[Type]           Type of the map
  --map.source-file.data             [IR]  bytes                Map data corresponding to the given map type
  --map.source-cloud-storage.bucket  [R]   string               Bucket name containing the map file
  --map.source-cloud-storage.object  [R]   string               Object path to the map file
  --map.annotations                  [O]   map<string, string>  Annotations is a generic key-value map
  --map-id                           [O]   string               Optional

CONNECTION FLAGS
  --address        string  Connect to address
  --force-trace    bool    Enable forced Google Cloud Trace header
  --insecure       bool    Make insecure connection (only on localhost)
  --token          string  Authenticate with a bearer token

OTHER FLAGS
  -f  --from-file    string  path to a JSON file containing the request payload
  -h  --help         bool    Show help for command
  -v  --verbose      bool    Enable verbose output
